cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual-inertial odometry and proposes a novel end-to-end selective sensor fusion framework for monocular VIO. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper focuses on improving the robustness of VIO for real-life issues, which is relevant to robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end deep learning approach for VIO. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel fusion strategy for dealing with imperfect sensory data, which is relevant to AI. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the estimation of trajectory using sensory data, which is relevant to systems and control.
